    "• **Admittanz-Karte (orange, gestrichelt)** = gespiegelte Y-Karte für Parallel-Komponenten.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Admittance card (orange, dashed)** = mirrored Y card for parallel components."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **EFHW-Choke:** FT-240-31 mit 7–10 Windungen — speziell für die Common-Mode-Probleme an EFHW-Antennen.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- **EFHW choke:** FT-240-31 with 7-10 turns - especially for common mode problems on EFHW antennas."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Konservative Berechnung:** Z_CM = X_L (rein induktiv). Bei Ferrit liegen die realen Werte im Verlust-Resonanz-Fenster oft 2–3× höher dank des Material-Imaginärteils μ\".": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Conservative calculation:** Z_CM = X_L (purely inductive). With ferrite, the real values in the loss-resonance window are often 2-3× higher thanks to the material imaginary part μ\"."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Linker Rand (−1, 0)** = Short (Kurzschluss, 0 Ω).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- **Left edge (-1, 0)** = Short (short circuit, 0 Ω)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Mitte (grüner Punkt)** = Z₀ Match, perfekt angepasst (VSWR 1:1).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Center (green dot)** = Z₀ match, perfectly matched (VSWR 1:1)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Mix 31** ist typisch beste Wahl für KW-Choke (1–10 MHz top, brauchbar bis 30 MHz). **Mix 43** für 5–50 MHz universell. **Mix 61** für VHF/UHF. **Mix 77** für NF (<2 MHz).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Mix 31** is typically the best choice for KW choke (1-10 MHz top, usable up to 30 MHz). **Mix 43** for 5-50 MHz universal. **Mix 61** for VHF/UHF. **Mix 77** for LF (<2 MHz)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Obere Halbebene** = induktive Last (X > 0).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Upper half plane** = inductive load (X > 0)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **R-Kreise (blau)** = konstanter Real-Anteil. **X-Bögen (lila)** = konstanter Imaginär-Anteil.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- R-circles (blue)** = constant real component. **X arcs (purple)** = constant imaginary component."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Rechter Rand (1, 0)** = Open (Leerlauf, ∞ Ω).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- **Right edge (1, 0)** = Open (idle, ∞ Ω)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Roter VSWR-Kreis** = alle Impedanzen mit gleichem VSWR wie die Last.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Red VSWR circle** = all impedances with the same VSWR as the load."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Standard-Empfehlung 100 W KW-Station:** FT-240-43 mit 10–14 Windungen Aircell-5 / RG-58 — deckt 80–10m sauber ab.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Standard recommendation 100 W HF station:** FT-240-43 with 10-14 turns Aircell-5 / RG-58 - covers 80-10m cleanly."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Untere Halbebene** = kapazitive Last (X < 0).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Lower half plane** = capacitive load (X < 0)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Wickel-Trick:** Windungen gleichmäßig um den Kern verteilen (nicht alle nebeneinander) — weniger Eigenkapazität, breiteres Sperrband.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Winding trick:** Distribute windings evenly around the core (not all next to each other) - less inherent capacitance, wider barrier tape."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• **Ziel: Z_CM ≥ 1 kΩ** auf den genutzten Bändern. **≥ 5 kΩ** ist optimal.": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Target: Z_CM ≥ 1 kΩ** on the bands used. **≥ 5 kΩ** is optimal."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• Activator-Punkte: pro Summit + UTC-Tag mit ≥ 4 QSOs zählen Base-Punkte aus der Summit-DB plus saisonaler Winterbonus (Nord 1. Dez – 15. März, Süd 1. Juni – 15. Sept).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Activator points: per Summit + UTC day with ≥ 4 QSOs count base points from the Summit DB plus seasonal winter bonus (North Dec. 1 - March 15, South June 1 - Sept. 15)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "• Activator-Refs = eindeutige Refs in myWwffRef + myWwffRefs (Hopping zählt jede Ref separat).": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "needs_review",
            "value": "- Activator-Refs = unique Refs in myWwffRef + myWwffRefs (hopping counts each Ref separately)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
